name: Award-Winning White Chicken Chili
author: Rjcunigan
summary: This chili is a family favorite! It has won several chili competitions and is a definite crowd-pleaser!
ingredients: 1 ¼ pounds skinless, boneless chicken breast
1 (10.5 ounce) can cream of chicken soup
1 (4 ounce) can chopped green chile peppers
½ cup shredded pepper Jack cheese, or to taste
directions: Layer chicken, great Northern beans, and corn into a slow cooker
Mix chicken broth, chicken soup, green chile peppers, and   together in a bowl; pour over chicken mixture
Cover and cook on Low until chicken is no longer pink in the center, 8 to 10 hours
Stir in sour cream and pepper Jack cheese; cover and cook until cheese is melted, 3 to 5 minutes
